# Calendar Domain Standards

## Calendars & locale
- Align with CLDR for month/weekday names and locale codes.
- ISO 8601 for Gregorian dates in config/API (`YYYY-MM-DD`).
- Week start from `LocaleProfile` (Saturday for Iran/Afghanistan).
- Numerals: `NumeralStyle::Persian` default; formatting in `format.rs` only.

## Countries
- Profiles: Iran, Afghanistan (Dari/Pashto), Tajikistan — extend via `CountryProfile` + JSON data.
- Prayer defaults per country: Tehran/Karachi/MWL methods; Hanafi for Afghanistan.

## Holidays JSON schema
- Fields: `name`, `month`, `day`, optional `year`, `lunar`, `kind` (national/religious/cultural).
- Document lunar holiday sources; mark approximate dates in UI when `lunar: true`.
- Keep holiday data in `data/holidays/{country}.json`; cities in `data/locations/`.

## Popup calendar grid
- 7-column grid using `LocaleProfile.weekday_short`.
- Highlight today (`today_color`), holidays (`holiday_color`), weekend days per country.
